ai-ja289:1.1_0: “We are not rid of desire, Great King,
ai-ja289:1.2_0: after staying in my home all alone—
ai-ja289:1.3_0: I wish to live in the village.
ai-ja289:2.3_0: And who on earth is full of dust,
ai-ja289:3.2_0: Among the brahmins from the city of Vedisa,
ai-ja289:3.3_0: he is the dust of his children,
ai-ja289:3.5_0: than I’m full of sacred flame.
ai-ja289:3.6_0: the covetous thing that falls away.”
